{
  "texts": [
    "We used coherence (Röder et al. 2015) as an evaluation metric to determine the optimal number of topics for each source.",
    "Coherence measures the degree of semantic similarity between the top N words of a topic.",
    "While there are different versions of coherence metrics available, we use the CV measure which is shown to have a high correlation with human judgment (Röder et al. 2015).",
    "Following previous studies (Benites-Lazaro et al. 2018b), we range the number of topics from 10 to 20 and obtain the coherence score as an average of three runs, each composed of 500 epochs.",
    "Table 5 shows the optimal number of topics identified for each source."
  ]
}